			</footer>

			<div class="comment-content"><p>Hi Ron,</p>
<p>Yes, I did evaluate Getopt::Simple. It has the right basic idea of using a hash for every option, to allow specifying various stuffs from usage message to default value to association with an environment variable. Getopt::Simple doesn&#8217;t yet allow expressing that an option is required. Other than that I think Getopt::Simple is mostly OK.</p>
<p id="comment-like-144" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://perlancar.wordpress.com/2016/12/24/getopt-modules-epilogue/?like_comment=144&#038;_wpnonce=b4aa7d7e1b" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="83450492"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-144" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p>
